page.title: 10Traffic in the west of area
page.content: Busk Lane is a busy route from Church Fenton to Ulleskelf and beyond,passing the main gate of R.A.F.Church Fenton. The military base,after a dormant period,was reactivated about 6 years ago,which led to an increase in traffic. Over 5 working days per week, about 15 tankers deliver jet fuel to the base. In addition,about 85 other vehicles pass through the main gate each week. Bus service 493 from Pontefract to Tadcaster and York runs along Busk Lane, there are 9 services per weekday each way,less on Saturday and none on Sunday. On Mondays only, a private bus makes the return trip to Selby for market day. School buses take over 11's to Sherburn High School or Tadcaster Grammar and under 11's to Church Fenton primary school.
